====================================================================================================
JxMake USB-GPIO Module II
====================================================================================================

This firmware is written for ATxmega128A4U.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The hardware SPI       implementation uses the standard ATxmega128A4U SPI   pins.
The hardware TWI       implementation uses the standard ATxmega128A4U TWI   pins.
The hardware UART/USRT implementation uses the standard ATxmega128A4U USART pins.

The software USRT      implementation uses the standard ATxmega128A4U SPI pins
                       (TXD=MOSI; RXD=MISO; XCK=SCK; [n]CS=[n]SS)

The software JTAG      implementation uses the standard ATxmega128A4U SPI and USART pins
                       (TDI=MOSI; TDO=MISO; TCK=SCK; nRST=nSS, nTRST=XCK, TMS=TXD)

Unlike the previous 'JxMake USB-GPIO Module' module, this 'JxMake USB-GPIO Module II' does not
control the TWI external pull-up resistors.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

When connected, this module will enumerate as two Virtual Serial Port:
    1. The first port is the primary port for performing most operations.
    2. The second port is the UART/USRT passthrough port. Its baudrate and data format can be
       configured using your operating system and programming language features, just like a typical
       serial port (but without the support for control signals such as RTS, CTS, and others). Note
       that the passthrough must be enabled (and disabled) via commands from the primary port.

====================================================================================================
